solver.explanations

Class Explanation

  • java.lang.Object
    • solver.explanations.Deduction
      • solver.explanations.Explanation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<Deduction>, Identity

    public class Explanation
extends Deduction
    An explanation is the combination of two sets: a set of deduction and a set of propagators. The deductions are stored in a list, and the uniqueness of elements is ensured during the add operation. This allows fast iteration over elements. The propagators are stored in the same way.
